nncAtmCongPointInfoTable.name: nncAtmCongPointInfoTable
nncAtmCongPointInfoTable.description: The ATM Congestion Point Information table. This table maintains various information for the congestion point specified.

nncAtmCongPointInfoEntry.name: nncAtmCongPointInfoEntry
nncAtmCongPointInfoEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Congestion Point Information table.

entPhysicalEntityInfoIndex.name: entPhysicalEntityInfoIndex
entPhysicalEntityInfoIndex.description: A unique value that identifies the physical entity, whether it supports Congestion Statistics or not. This value is equivalent to the value of PhysicalIndex.

nncAtmCongPointInfoIndex.name: nncAtmCongPointInfoIndex
nncAtmCongPointInfoIndex.description: A unique value between 1 and 8 that identifies the congestion point on an entity which supports Congestion Statistics.

nncAtmCongPointHardwareType.name: nncAtmCongPointHardwareType
nncAtmCongPointHardwareType.description: A unique value, 1 to 99, that identifies the current hardware type of the congestion point. See Tables 1 and 2 for further details.

nncAtmCongStatsRawTable.name: nncAtmCongStatsRawTable
nncAtmCongStatsRawTable.description: The ATM Raw Congestion Statistics table. This table maintains raw per quality of service statistics since the interface was started.

nncAtmCongStatsRawEntry.name: nncAtmCongStatsRawEntry
nncAtmCongStatsRawEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Raw Congestion Statistics table.

entPhysicalEntityRawIndex.name: entPhysicalEntityRawIndex
entPhysicalEntityRawIndex.description: A unique value that identifies the physical entity, whether it supports Congestion Statistics or not. This value is equivalent to the value of PhysicalIndex.

nncAtmCongPointRawIndex.name: nncAtmCongPointRawIndex
nncAtmCongPointRawIndex.description: A unique value between 1 and 8 that identifies the congestion point on an entity which supports Congestion Statistics.

nncAtmCongStatsQOSRawIndex.name: nncAtmCongStatsQOSRawIndex
nncAtmCongStatsQOSRawIndex.description: A number between 1 and 11 that identifies the quality of service on which the set of statistics was collected for an entity. The following table describes the quality of service categories available and their corresponding index. Quality of Service Quality of Service Index ------------------ ------------------------ CBR 1 UBR 2 rt-VBR1 3 rt-VBR2 4 nrt-VBR1-2 5 nrt-VBR3 6 ABR 7 CBR-rtVBR 8 nrt-VBR/UBR 9 ABR/UBR 10 nrt-VBR 11

nncAtmCongStatsTotalCellsDiscarded.name: nncAtmCongStatsTotalCellsDiscarded
nncAtmCongStatsTotalCellsDiscarded.description: Total number of cells discarded due to congestion.

nncAtmCongStatsClp0CellsDiscarded.name: nncAtmCongStatsClp0CellsDiscarded
nncAtmCongStatsClp0CellsDiscarded.description: Number of CLP 0 cells discarded due to congestion.

nncAtmCongStatsLowCongestedSeconds.name: nncAtmCongStatsLowCongestedSeconds
nncAtmCongStatsLowCongestedSeconds.description: Number of seconds the congestion point was in the Low Congestion State.

nncAtmCongStatsMediumCongestedSeconds.name: nncAtmCongStatsMediumCongestedSeconds
nncAtmCongStatsMediumCongestedSeconds.description: Number of seconds the congestion point was in the Medium Congestion State.

nncAtmCongStatsSevereCongestedSeconds.name: nncAtmCongStatsSevereCongestedSeconds
nncAtmCongStatsSevereCongestedSeconds.description: Number of seconds the congestion point was in the Severe Congestion State.

nncAtmCongStatsTotalSeconds.name: nncAtmCongStatsTotalSeconds
nncAtmCongStatsTotalSeconds.description: Total number of seconds the congestion point was in the Normal, Low, Medium, or Severe congestion states.

nncAtmCongStatsCurrentCongestionState.name: nncAtmCongStatsCurrentCongestionState
nncAtmCongStatsCurrentCongestionState.description: Current congestion state of the congestion point - one of Normal, Low, Medium, or Severe. When the current congestion state is determined, the corresponding congestion time counter will increment.

nncAtmCongStatsAlarmStatus.name: nncAtmCongStatsAlarmStatus
nncAtmCongStatsAlarmStatus.description: Current alarm status - either ON or OFF. When a congestion point has been severely congested for longer than the allowable threshold time the value of this object is set to congStatsAlarmOn. When severe congestion clears, the value of this object is set to congStatsAlarmOff.

nncAtmCongStatsVirtualBandwidthAvail.name: nncAtmCongStatsVirtualBandwidthAvail
nncAtmCongStatsVirtualBandwidthAvail.description: Percentage of virtual bandwidth that is available for use for each quality of service.

nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlState.name: nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlState
nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlState.description: The state of the interval in the interval statistics interface. Possible states are: normal (1) - normal interval; no change in time and no resets nonexistent (2) - statistics do not exist for this interval userReset (3) - the user has reset statistics collection during this interval start (4) - this is the first interval timeChange (5) - the system time has been changed during this interval

nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlAbsolute.name: nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlAbsoluteIntervalNumber
nncAtmCongStatsCurrentShortIntvlAbsolute.description: The absolute interval number of the stats interval in the interval statistics interface. If the interval is not defined yet, the absolute interval number will be -1. For the short, 15 minutes intervals the possible values are: absolute interval interval index start end ----------------- ------------ 1 00:00 00:15 2 00:15 00:30 3 00:30 00:45 ... ... ... 95 23:30 23:45 96 23:45 00:00

nncAtmCongStatsShortIntvlTable.name: nncAtmCongStatsShortIntvlTable
nncAtmCongStatsShortIntvlTable.description: The ATM Short Interval Congestion Statistics table. This table maintains short interval statistics per quality of service since the interface was started. There are 96 intervals, where the first interval (i.e., interval with index 1) is the most recently completed interval and the length of each interval is 15 minutes.
